==Synonyms in other languages==
The stevia plant ''stevia rebaudiana bertoni'' (also known as ''eupatorium rebaudianum bertoni'') is known by the following names in other languages: [http://www.plantnames.unimelb.edu.au/Sorting/Stevia.html]
*[[Chinese]]: 甜菊 (Tian ju), 甜菊叶 (Tian ju ye - stevia leaf)
*[[English]] : Candy leaf, Stevia, Sugar leaf, Sweetleaf (USA), Sweet honey leaf (Australia), Sweet herb of [[Paraguay]]
*[[French]]: Stévia
*[[German]]: Stevia
*[[Italian]]: Piccolo arbusto con foglio più dolce, Stevia
*[[Japanese]]: アマハステビア (Amaha sutebia)
*[[Marathi]]: Madhu Parani 
*[[Portuguese]]: Capim doce, Erva doce, Estévia (Brazil), Folhas da stévia, Stévia
*[[Sanskrit]]: Madhu Patra
*[[Spanish]]: Caá-ché, Hierba dulce, Ka´a he´ê (Guaraníes - Natives of [[Paraguay]]), Stevia del norte de Paraguay, Yerba dulce
*[[Swedish]]: Stevia
*[[Tamil]]: Seeni Tulsi 
*[[Telugu]]: Madhu Patri 
*[[Thai]]: Satiwia, หญ้าหวาน (Ya wan - [[Bangkok]])